The paper discusses the fundamental performance limitations of online machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses entropic analysis from information theory (cs.IT) and the innovations approach from prediction theory, which are relevant subfields. The paper discusses supervised learning, semi-supervised learning, and unsupervised learning, which are all subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the implications of the results in analyzing the fundamental limits of generalization, which is a topic that falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
